   370	## 4. Tracker detection-threshold false-alarm analysis (U-T1 finding F9)
   371	
   372	Finding F9 (`DECISIONS.md` D36) routes the `pnt-tracker` default detection threshold of **32**
   373	(15.1 dB) here for a probability-of-false-alarm (PFA) analysis. The tracker's per-block quality
   374	statistic is `Q = peak_delay_bin_power / mean_of_the_other_delay_bins_power`, maximised over
   375	the frequency-hypothesis grid (`crates/pnt-tracker/src/lib.rs`). The fixture geometry is
   376	**256 delay bins × 256 frequency bins** (Fs = 8192, N = 256, 32 Hz coarse grid). Measured
   377	noise-only quality statistics over 4000 pure-noise blocks: **median 11.5, p99 15.7, max 20.0**
   378	(zero false alarms at threshold 32), from `.orchestration/reports/U-T1-review-opus-measurements.md`.
   379	
   380	> **Provenance caveat (carried from the artifact).** The 4000-block quantiles are **review
   381	> measurements produced by the U-T1 deep-review seat's own probes** (pnt-tracker commit
   382	> 54005dd, probes run in-worktree then removed), **not shipped-test evidence and not
   383	> reproducible from the committed suite** — the committed noise test covers only **24 blocks**
   384	> (U-T1 report). They are archived as citable evidence but carry no reproducible seed/command.
   385	> Everything below that leans on these quantiles inherits that reproducibility gap; see the §4.4
   386	> assumptions.
   387	
   388	### 4.1 Analytic model
   389	
   390	**Statistic → Fisher's g.** Within one frequency hypothesis, the N_d = 256 circular-correlation
   391	delay-bin powers are (under the assumptions below) i.i.d. exponential (complex-Gaussian
   392	magnitude-squared). Let `S` be their sum and `P_max` the peak. The code's floor is the mean of
   393	the **other** N_d−1 bins, so
   394	
   395	```
   396	Q = P_max / [ (S − P_max) / (N_d − 1) ] = (N_d − 1) · g / (1 − g),   where g = P_max / S.
   397	```
   398	
   399	`g` is exactly **Fisher's g-statistic** (largest ordinate / sum) for the max of N_d i.i.d.
   400	exponentials, whose exact exceedance is
   401	
   402	```
   403	P(g > x) = Σ_{j=1}^{⌊1/x⌋} (−1)^{j−1} · C(N_d, j) · (1 − j·x)^{N_d − 1}.
   404	```
   405	
   406	Inverting the map, threshold `Q` corresponds to `g_thr = Q / (Q + N_d − 1)`. For the reported
   407	quality the tracker also **maximises over the N_f = 256 frequency rows**, so the per-block PFA
   408	is bounded by a union over rows:
   409	
   410	```
   411	P_block(Q) ≤ N_f · P(g > g_thr) ≈ N_f · N_d · (1 − g_thr)^{N_d − 1}
   412	           = N_cells · (1 − g_thr)^{N_d − 1},   N_cells = 65536.
   413	```
   414	
   415	(At the operating threshold **Q = 32** the leading Fisher term dominates the next by ~12.7
   416	orders of magnitude, so the single-term approximation is exact for the PFA figure. This is
   417	**not** true across the lower validation thresholds — near the median `Q = 12.06` the second
   418	term is ~5e-4 of the first (≈3.3 orders), and near p99 ~5.2 orders — so the validation-table
   419	computations below retain the full Fisher sum, and the "single leading term" simplification is
   420	scoped to `Q = 32` only.)
   421	
   422	### 4.2 Model validation against the measured noise statistics
   423	
   424	Inverting `P_block` for the quantile thresholds and comparing to the empirical 4000-block
   425	statistics (independent-cell prediction vs observed):
   426	
   427	| Quantile | P_block | Q predicted (i.i.d. cells) | Q observed |
   428	|---|---:|---:|---:|
   429	| median | 0.5 | 12.06 | **11.5** |
   430	| p99 | 0.01 | 16.19 | **15.7** |
   431	| max (≈1/4000) | 2.5e-4 | 20.14 | **20.0** |
   432	
   433	The model reproduces all three empirical quantiles to within ~0.5 in Q. The observed values sit
   434	**slightly below** the independent-cell prediction, and the gap narrows toward the tail. This is
   435	the signature of **mild positive inter-cell dependence**: positive correlation among the
   436	searched cells **reduces the effective number of independent trials**, so the independent-cell
   437	union calculation predicts a *larger* maximum-tail than reality — i.e. for the row/search
   438	dependence alone, the independent-cell PFA is an **over**-estimate (**conservative**), not
   439	optimistic. **Correction of the previous draft:** the earlier claim that the lower empirical
   440	quantiles made the model "slightly optimistic" and therefore warranted inflation was
   441	**direction-inverted and is withdrawn**. The lower empirical quantiles cannot, on their own,
   442	justify inflating the PFA. The legitimate reasons to carry margin above the analytic estimate
   443	are the **separate** modelling-limit caveats in §4.4 (non-ideal reference sidelobes → non-
   444	exponential marginals; interference and non-stationarity), which act on the *marginal
   445	distribution* and can make real-capture tails **heavier** in a way this fixture cannot bound —
   446	distinct from, and not inferable from, the conservative row-dependence effect.
   447	
   448	### 4.3 PFA at threshold 32, and the false-alarm rate
   449	
   450	At Q = 32: `g_thr = 32/287 = 0.1115`, giving
   451	
   452	```
   453	P_block(32) ≈ 65536 · (255/287)^255 = 5.30e-9   (ANALYTIC-MODEL estimate only).
   454	```
   455	
   456	**This 5.3e-9 is the analytic-model figure, not an empirically validated PFA.** 4000 noise
   457	blocks (and they are review probes, not shipped tests — provenance caveat above) can bound a
   458	probability of order ~1e-3, not ~5e-9; they can show threshold 32 sat ~12 above the observed
   459	noise-only max of 20.0 in that run, but they **cannot validate a false-alarm probability near
   460	5e-9 nor justify any specific numeric bracket** (e.g. the earlier "order 1e-8" bracket is
   461	**withdrawn** — the non-ideal-reference/interference tails of §4.4 admit an *unquantified*
   462	heavier real-capture tail that could lie well above 1e-8). As an illustrative *model* rate: the
   463	fixture block is 256/8192 = 31.25 ms (~32 blocks/s per tracked signal), so the model per-tracker
   464	FA rate is ≈ 32 × 5.3e-9 ≈ 1.7e-7 s⁻¹ → ~68 model-days between false alarms per tracker — a
   465	figure of the *analytic model at the fixture geometry only*, superseded by real-capture
   466	measurement (§4.5).
   467	
   468	### 4.4 Assumptions and caveats (including cell correlation)
   469	
   470	- **A1 — i.i.d. exponential delay bins.** Exact only for white input noise and an ideal
   471	  delta-autocorrelation reference. **Real Starlink PSS/SSS, Iridium, Orbcomm sequences have
   472	  non-zero autocorrelation sidelobes** → off-peak bins are correlated and not identically
   473	  distributed → the effective independent-cell count is **below** N_d and the tail is **heavier**
   474	  than exponential. This is the dominant reason the synthetic-fixture PFA cannot be trusted as
   475	  the production PFA. (No real sequences are shipped — U-T1 `[UNVERIFIED]`.)
   476	- **A2 — row union bound (conservative).** The N_f frequency rows are **positively correlated**
   477	  (same IQ block; the 32 Hz grid equals the FFT bin spacing Fs/N, so a row shift is a circular
   478	  re-index), so the union bound over-counts and `P_block` is an **upper** bound; positive
   479	  dependence reduces the effective independent-trial count. The empirical quantiles sitting
   480	  *below* the independent-cell prediction are consistent with this conservative direction. This
   481	  effect **cannot** justify inflating the PFA — inflation is warranted only by A1/A3 (§4.2).
   482	- **A3 — stationary white Gaussian noise.** Real captures carry coloured noise, narrowband
   483	  interference lines, ADC quantization, dropouts and sea-surface multipath. The per-row CFAR
   484	  normalisation self-adapts to broadband level changes but **not** to a narrowband interferer
   485	  that mimics a correlation peak → real tails fatten.
   486	- **A4 — fixture geometry ≠ production.** Fs = 8192, N = 256, 32 Hz grid, 256×256 cells are the
   487	  **test fixture**. Production is 2.5–5 MHz bandwidth with real-length sequences; both N_cells and
   488	  the block duration change, so **both the PFA and the block rate must be recomputed for
   489	  production geometry**. Threshold 32 is validated *for the fixture*, not frozen for production.
   490	- **A5 — evidence provenance and reproducibility.** The 4000-block quantiles are the U-T1 deep-
   491	  review seat's **in-worktree probes** (commit 54005dd, probes removed after the run),
   492	  **irreproducible from the committed suite** (24-block noise test only), with no recorded
   493	  seed/command. They corroborate the analytic model's *shape* but are not a reproducible PFA
   494	  measurement; §4.5's validation plan therefore requires a fresh, recorded, real-capture
   495	  characterisation before any production freeze.
   496	
   497	### 4.5 Proposed threshold policy
   498	
   499	1. **Keep the peak-to-mean-of-others ratio (CFAR) statistic.** Its scale-invariance to input
   500	   noise power is a genuine robustness property for a maritime RF environment with a changing
   501	   noise floor — prefer it over any absolute-power threshold.
   502	2. **Set the threshold from a target per-block PFA via the Fisher-g model scaled to the actual
   503	   production search volume**, not a magic constant: solve `N_cells^prod · (1 − g)^{N_d^prod − 1}
   504	   = PFA_target` with `g = Q/(Q + N_d^prod − 1)`. This makes the threshold grow ~logarithmically
   505	   with search volume (Bonferroni/CFAR-consistent) as N and the Doppler span change.
   506	3. **Choose `PFA_target` from a false-observation budget, not from minimising PFA.** The tracker
   507	   is the **first** gate; a spurious detection still faces the EKF per-component 1-DOF chi-square
   508	   NIS gate, the 5° elevation mask, the ephemeris-age gate, the pass-nuisance state and cross-
   509	   sensor residuals. A per-block PFA of ~1e-7 to ~1e-8 in production geometry (≈ <1 false
   510	   detection per hours-to-days per tracker) is a reasonable starting budget, leaving the EKF gate
   511	   as the second line. (At the fixture, ~1e-7 corresponds to Q ≈ 29; 32 gives ~5e-9.)
   512	4. **The missed-detection cost sets the *upper* bound on the threshold.** Too high → fewer
   513	   accepted Doppler observations → weaker geometry → larger protection limits → authority harder
   514	   to sustain and convergence slower. The threshold is a **detection/false-alarm trade-off to be
   515	   set jointly with the per-constellation link budget** (C/N₀), which is currently `[UNVERIFIED]`
   516	   (no per-constellation C/N₀ measurements). Do **not** maximise for low PFA in isolation.
   517	5. **Validate on real noise-only and weak-signal captures**, using this Fisher-g model only as
   518	   the analytic scaffold. Deploy a threshold set from measured real-capture noise statistics with
   519	   explicit margin above the measured noise-only max (the fixture shows 32 ≈ 12 above max 20).
   520	
   521	**Fixture recommendation:** retain the explicit default **32** (analytic-model PFA ~5e-9;
   522	observed ~12 above the noise-only max in the review run) as a conservative provisional. **Production threshold: `[UNVERIFIED]`**, to be
   523	re-derived per §4.5(2)–(5) once real sequences, production geometry and per-constellation link
   524	budgets exist. The tracker threshold is **not** an `AuthorityParams` field and is not in the
   525	appendix; it is nonetheless a steering-relevant `[UNVERIFIED]` value with its own freeze path.
   526	
   527	---
   528	
   529	## 5. Open design issues registered by this proposal
   530	
   531	### 5.1 Single-scalar caution/revoke thresholds vs per-profile protection limits
   532	
   533	`AuthorityParams` carries `ProtectionLimits` **per profile** (aided/denied, 8× apart on
   534	position) but `caution_enter`/`caution_clear`/`revoke_threshold` are **single scalars** compared
   535	against the same metre metric. With the aided PL at 12 m and the caution band referenced to the
   536	100 m denied envelope, **aided mode has no caution pre-alert** — the profile PL revokes before
   537	the caution metric is ever reached. This proposal makes the band meaningful in the mode where it
   538	matters most (denied/degrading) and accepts the aided-mode gap. **Recommended contracts change:
   539	make the caution band (and revoke backstop) per-profile**, matching `ProtectionLimits`. Routed
   540	to the contracts owner as a proposed v6 refinement; not assumed here.
   541	
   542	### 5.2 Coverage-factor / acceptance-percentile / covariance-shape coupling
   543	
   544	The `k = 2` position factor and the velocity/heading mappings all stand in for the baseline's
   545	**unfrozen acceptance-percentile/confidence definition**. When that definition is frozen (baseline
   546	obligation), every §1 limit must be re-derived consistently — a single coupled freeze, not
   547	independent. Additionally, the velocity mapping assumes **isotropic, Gaussian per-axis
   548	covariance** (§1.2 anisotropy limitation): a scalar DRMS gate does not guarantee a per-axis
   549	bound under the anisotropic covariance LEO geometry produces. **Recommended: freeze a covariance-
   550	shape rule (or adopt per-axis velocity/heading gates) alongside the percentile.** Routed to the
   551	contracts/baseline owner with §5.1.
   552	
   553	### 5.3 Values with the weakest evidentiary support
   554	
   555	`t_dr` (no LEO-gap replay statistics), the aided velocity PL 0.014 m/s (achievability unproven;
   556	4 Hz tracker scale is fixture-only), and the human-factors dwells/`T_ack` (no trial evidence)
   557	are the least-anchored proposals. See the summary paragraph.
   558	
   559	### 5.4 `AuthorityParams`/CONTRACTS lacks per-source freshness fields — enforcement gap
   560	
   561	The `SAFETY_CASE.md` §1/§5 fail-closed register includes **per-source freshness deadlines**
   562	(IMU/magnetometer/speed-log/ephemeris), but `AuthorityParams` (CONTRACTS v5) and its
   563	`is_complete()` completeness check do **not** carry them. **A fully-populated `AuthorityParams`
   564	therefore passes `is_complete()` while these register items remain unfrozen** — the code-level
   565	fail-closed gate does not cover the entire safety-case register. Proposed values are in §2.4.
   566	**Contracts-owner action item (proposed v6):** add IMU/magnetometer/speed-log freshness fields
   567	(seconds) to `AuthorityParams` and to `is_complete()`, and either add an ephemeris-freshness
   568	field or record that ephemeris freshness is governed by `t_eph`. Until then these deadlines must
   569	be enforced upstream (executive/integrity ingress) and their freeze tracked outside
   570	`is_complete()`. Routed to the contracts owner; not assumed resolved here.
   571	
