   574	## 6. Machine-readable appendix — `AuthorityParams`
   575	
   576	The block below **mirrors the flat `AuthorityParams` struct** (`crates/pnt-integrity/src/lib.rs`):
   577	the nine scalar fields are **top-level** (before any table header, as TOML requires) with their
   578	exact Rust names, and `aided`/`denied` are `[aided]`/`[denied]` tables mirroring the nested
   579	`ProtectionLimits`. It deserializes field-for-field into a serde mirror of the struct — there is
   580	no intermediate `[timers]`/`[thresholds]` grouping (a prior draft's non-deserializable
   581	organisational nesting is removed).
   582	
   583	```toml
