   588	#  This block grants NO authority. Per SAFETY_CASE.md §1 (D17 fail-closed
   589	#  gate), an unfrozen authority-contract parameter is a CLOSED GATE: the
   590	#  supervisor cannot grant steering authority while any field is unverified.
   591	#  Freezing any value requires (a) the evidence in that parameter's §1-§3
   592	#  validation plan AND (b) a signed DECISIONS.md line. Until then the
   593	#  corresponding supervisor Option<f64> should remain None.
   594	#
   595	#  Shape mirrors the flat AuthorityParams struct: scalar fields top-level with
   596	#  exact Rust names; aided/denied as ProtectionLimits sub-tables.
   597	#  Units: position/velocity SI (m, m/s); heading rad; caution/revoke metric in
   598	#  m (horizontal_accuracy_m); all *_s timers in seconds.
   599	#  NOTE: per-source freshness deadlines (§2.4) are NOT fields of this struct
   600	#  (register gap §5.4) and appear in a SEPARATE block below.
   601	# ============================================================================
   602	
   603	# --- Scalar fields (top-level; exact AuthorityParams field names) ----------
   604	t_lease_s        = 1.0       # §2.1  < GPS_TIMEOUT_MS (4 s)              [UNVERIFIED]
   605	t_dr_s           = 120.0     # §2.2  DR-authority backstop; weak evidence [UNVERIFIED]
   606	t_eph_s          = 21600.0   # §2.3  6 h SupGP age gate (baseline)       [UNVERIFIED]
