   653	
   654	This document is **subordinate to `DESIGN_BASELINE.md` (normative) and `SAFETY_CASE.md`**; where
   655	either governs, it governs. It adds no sensor, estimator or acceptance requirement and revises
     1	# U-T1 Opus review — archived Monte-Carlo measurements (2026-07-23)
     2	
     3	Provenance: produced by the U-T1 deep-review seat's independent probes against pnt-tracker
     4	commit 54005dd (probes run in-worktree, then removed; full review in session transcript,
     5	summary in DECISIONS D36). Archived here as citable evidence for downstream analysis
     6	(PARAMS_PROPOSAL). These are REVIEW measurements, not shipped-test evidence: the committed
     7	suite's noise test covers 24 blocks only.
     8	
     9	- Discriminator frequency-error 1σ: 0.059 / 0.155 / 0.481 Hz at C/N0 = 78 / 70 / 62 dB-Hz
    10	  (2000 seeds each; max |error| 1.6 Hz at 62 dB-Hz).
    11	- Coarse-bin-only error for the four fixture offsets: 6.75–14 Hz (all > the 4 Hz tolerance,
    12	  proving the tolerance discriminates a broken interpolator).
    13	- Noise-only quality statistic (256×256 search, fixture config): median 11.5, p99 15.7,
    14	  max 20.0 over 4000 blocks; zero false alarms at threshold 32 in 4000 blocks.
    15	- Signal quality at C/N0 62/65 dB-Hz: 186–191 (saturation ~190 for C/N0 ≥ ~62 dB-Hz).
    16	- Second-seat spot-check (60 trials, 65 dB-Hz): noise-only max-quality range ~9.7–15.9,
    17	  consistent with the above.
    70	vessel-axis signs, so calibration metadata, not an assumed convention, is authoritative
    71	until that physical convention is verified.
    72	
    73	### On-disk formats (resolves v1 format deferral)
    74	
    75	Every run is an append-only, schema-versioned directory. Its manifest records run UUID,
    76	schema versions, optional absolute RFC 3339 UTC creation time, monotonic epoch metadata,
    77	configuration hash, calibration IDs, software revision, hardware/channel setup, ephemeris
    78	snapshot identity and file hashes. Segments are atomically finalised and recoverable after
    79	an unclean stop.
    80	
    81	- Raw IQ consists of independently recoverable fixed-duration segments of interleaved,
    82	  coherent, lossless RX-channel samples plus sidecar/header metadata: representation,
    83	  endianness, sample rate, centre frequency, bandwidth, gain, allocation, external-reference
    84	  state, first-sample monotonic and optional UTC time, sample count, gaps/overruns and
    85	  calibration/configuration identity. ADC packing remains `[UNVERIFIED]`.
    86	- The measurement journal is a checksummed, length-delimited binary stream of exact v2 bus
    87	  envelopes, segmented and indexed by monotonic time, source and message kind. It includes
    88	  inputs, decisions, propagation/update records, solutions, integrity/authority events,
    89	  alarms and publication outcomes. Unknown required schema versions are hard errors.
    90	- The truth journal is a physically and logically separate versioned, length-delimited
    91	  record stream containing source ID, sample time, host receipt time, optional UTC,
    92	  position/velocity/heading truth, covariance, quality and provenance. Online estimator
    93	  and rejection-gate APIs have no read edge to it.
    94	
    95	The reviewed design leaves all three binary container codecs `[UNVERIFIED]`; v2 therefore
    96	fixes record boundaries, required metadata, separation, version/error behaviour and recovery
    97	semantics, but deliberately does not name a codec.
    98	
    99	### Time ownership (resolves v1 ownership deferral)
   100	
   101	The clock/time service is the sole owner of runtime time. It establishes the process
   102	monotonic epoch and alone stamps ingress and defines ordering, freshness, deadlines,
   103	authority leases and watchdogs. Adapters may supply device counters or UTC labels only as
   104	measurements. The service maintains and journals an uncertainty-bearing device/monotonic/UTC
   105	mapping. Persistent records carry nanoseconds from the run monotonic epoch and optional
   106	absolute RFC 3339 UTC. Estimator receiver-clock bias/drift are filter states, not system
   107	time, and GNSS must never silently discipline runtime time or the SDR reference.
   108	
   109	### Rate contract (resolves v1 rate deferral)
   110	
   111	| Interface | v2 contract |
   112	|---|---|
   113	| SDR processing bandwidth | Tracker-selected 2.5--5 MHz per active correlation channel; sample rate `[UNVERIFIED]` |
   114	| IMU to executive | 100 Hz nominal (**estimate**); every accepted sample propagates state and covariance |
   115	| Each magnetometer | 10 Hz nominal (**estimate**) |

